Posted: Thu Apr 18, 2013 1:07 pm
Alanthiras wrote:Wouldn't that be like double gravity? :xI'm quite fine here on lovely Terra thank you! I'm not going to do the math just now, but gravity on the surface of a planet is inversely related to the distance squared to the core.In other words, while the gravitational strength of the planet grows exponentially to its radius, what you feel decreases by the same rate relative to the radius. I believe you could have a planet with twice the radius and yet have Earth-like surface gravity, as long as the density is similar.
